ate, at about 2:00 p.m, Hamisu, the second convict, went to Yahaya’s shop at Kwari Market to buy some goods, while there, he collected his phone to calculate the amount of what he bought but in the process, he ran off with his Nokia phone. “The two phones were recovered by the police”, Soron-Dinki said, after explaining that the offences contravened sections 286 and 308 of the Penal Code. Vanguard News Nigeria A Karu Chief Magistrates' Court, Abuja,on Friday ordered that a 15-year-old deaf and dumb boy, be given 14 strokes of the cane, for stealing N10,000. The convict, a primary school pupil, was arraigned by the police before Chief Magistrate Hadiza Dodo, on a two-count charge of house breaking and theft.… February 7, 2014 In "News" A Magistrates' Court sitting at 'Yan-Azara, Tudun-Wada, Zaria, has convicted one Lukman Ibrahim, 27, of Turunku Road, Tudun-Wada, Zaria, to two years in prison with 12 strokes of the cane for theft. May 16, 2015 In "News" An Abuja Senior Magistrates’ Court on Monday ordered that two men, Ibrahim Salisu and Sani Adamu, be given eight strokes of the cane each for concealing stolen property. October 8, 2012 In "News"